{"questionId":"9072756","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Moon has no atmosphere and orbits the Earth. The diagram shows the Moon with rays of light from the Sun that are incident at 90° to the axis of rotation of the Moon.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/823da7e70af7d3cfbfe0a9f0f12edf4c25fa0eb0.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Outline why a&nbsp;force acts on the Moon.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>gravitational attraction/force/field «of the planet/Moon» ✔</p>\n<p><em>Do not accept “gravity”</em>.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072756","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline why a force acts on the Moon.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.2 – Newton’s law of gravitation","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}